Grapefruit juice had already come under fire because it was held responsible for increasing the effects of some antiarrhythmic medicines, antibiotics, antihisymoitis, antihistamines and neurological effects to be considered toxic.
The Italian Agency of the drug had reported it in an information bulletin two years ago alerting doctors and patients not to underestimate the danger deriving from this mix and to pay attention to what is drunk in the event that you take drugs such as Diazepam or Methadone.
