Two years later, betting on marine energy is increasingly and among these companies always devoted to traditional energy.
“Chevron is studying ocean energy technologies,” a spokesman for a subsidiary of a subsidiary of the U.S. oil giant told the economic newspaper Wall Street Journal, “and is considering the possibility of cooperating with us,” the statement said.
